    <stitle>530 and DT-466/408 Diesel Engine Diagnostics (1993) - ENGINE PERFORMANCE ANALYSIS GUIDES - ENGINE TEST
        NOMENCLATURE
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>ENGINE TEST NOMENCLATURE</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="proctype" graphiccount="1">
            <title>INJECTION PUMP TIMING</title>
            <para>Injection pump static timing is checked with the engine stopped -- NOT RUNNING. The engine must be
                rotated so the #1 piston is at the top of its compression stroke and the timing mark on the vibration
                damper is in alignment with the timing mark on the timing indicator
                <hotlnk xrefid="ef1100301">(Figure 3.2)</hotlnk>
                which indicates static timing in degrees Before Top Dead Center (BTDC). Static timing is not the same
                for all engine models.
                <emph type="bold">Refer to Test 4 in Section 5 of this manual.</emph>
            </para>
            <figure id="ef1100301" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="eg3017" filename="../figeg3/EG3017.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 3.2 Injection Pump Timing Verification</caption>
            </figure>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
